Re: Informal journal entry
by Hyperworm » Fri 09.18.2009 6:40 pm My feelings here are as follows(as usual, someone correct me if I'm wrong -- except you of course, Mr.Paper )I think this "na" is okay. It's like "they were pretty good, as I recall!" / "thinking back, the burritos were pretty good!". Like a reflection on past events.The construction "ni tsuite wa" is legal but a little overblown for this situation (I'd translate it as "concerning" rather than "for"). "hirugohan wa buritou datta" might be best? (it has a long o)I think "uchi" is fine too. >_>For the first sentence maybe "sugoku tanoshii ichinichi o sugoshita" or something like that? Anyway I think "ichinichi" is better than "hi" here."sumaseta to" is not grammatical with the meaning you want it to have, but I'm not sure what the best thing is to replace it with.
