Re: Informal journal entry
by furrykef » Fri 09.18.2009 7:19 pm Hyperworm wrote:The construction "ni tsuite wa" is legalI stand corrected. I forgot that "wa" can be tacked on to darn near anything... (I'm still sure it was invalid in the other thread, though, which had "o" rather than "wa" after "tsuite".)I think "uchi" is fine too. >_>Hmm. You may be right. It seems I don't grasp the difference between "ie" and "uchi" as well as I thought I did...- Kef
